# release.env — deployment-local OVERRIDES + secrets (TEMPLATE).
#
# Copy to `release.env` (gitignored, per-machine) ONLY if you need to override a
# canonical default or add a secret. BOTH launch paths source it:
#   ./start_proxy.sh   (working-tree proxy)   — sourced; caller env still wins
#   ./run_release.sh   (official :7800)       — sourced
#
# You do NOT need this file for normal operation: start_proxy.sh already enables
# the canonical proxy stance by default (no setup on a fresh clone) —
#   WS_SPAWNER_HINT=1            spawner grammar hint into spawn-capable agents
#   WS_OMIT_DEFAULT=useremail    strip # userEmail from every subagent spawn
#   STRIP_COMPACT_CACHE=1, WARMTH_BLOCK_COLD_PING=1, WARMTH_LOG_FILE=1
# This file is only for turning something OFF, changing a value, or secrets.
#
# Format: plain KEY=VALUE, one per line; # comments and blank lines ignored.
# Anything here overrides the code default but a caller-supplied env var still
# wins over this file (e.g. `WS_SPAWNER_HINT=0 ./start_proxy.sh`).

# --- examples (uncomment + edit to use) ---

# Turn the spawner hint OFF for this machine:
# WS_SPAWNER_HINT=0

# Change the omit floor (comma- or space-separated; empty disables it):
# WS_OMIT_DEFAULT=useremail
# WS_OMIT_DEFAULT=

# Subscriber callback bearer token (secret — the real reason this file is gitignored):
# SUBSCRIBERS_TOKEN=change-me
